  "title": "Bitwise OR of Adjacent Elements",
  "titleSlug": "bitwise-or-of-adjacent-elements",
  "difficulty": "Easy",
  "content": "<p>Given an array <code>nums</code> of length <code>n</code>, return an array <code>answer</code> of length <code>n - 1</code> such that <code>answer[i] = nums[i] | nums[i + 1]</code> where <code>|</code> is the bitwise <code>OR</code> operation.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong class=\"example\">Example 1:</strong></p>\n\n<div class=\"example-block\">\n<p><strong>Input:</strong> <span class=\"example-io\">nums = [1,3,7,15]</span></p>\n\n<p><strong>Output:</strong> <span class=\"example-io\">[3,7,15]</span></p>\n</div>\n\n<p><strong class=\"example\">Example 2:</strong></p>\n\n<div class=\"example-block\">\n<p><strong>Input:</strong> <span class=\"example-io\">nums = [8,4,2]</span></p>\n\n<p><strong>Output:</strong> <span class=\"example-io\">[12,6]</span></p>\n</div>\n\n<p><strong class=\"example\">Example 3:</strong></p>\n\n<div class=\"example-block\">\n<p><strong>Input:</strong> <span class=\"example-io\">nums = [5,4,9,11]</span></p>\n\n<p><strong>Output:</strong> <span class=\"example-io\">[5,13,11]</span></p>\n</div>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Constraints:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li><code>2 &lt;= nums.length &lt;= 100</code></li>\n\t<li><code>0 &lt;= nums[i]&nbsp;&lt;= 100</code></li>\n</ul>\n",
  "hints": [
    "Iterate over array and calculate each element of the resulting array using <code>|</code> operation."
